02:59.336 --> 03:02.004
- Drop your weapons!
- Hands where we can see them!

03:02.073 --> 03:05.107
[ footsteps approaching ]

03:05.176 --> 03:10.080
I am not here to fight,
but to give you this.

03:10.148 --> 03:14.985
- The Forge of Solus Prime.
- Could be rigged to blow.

03:15.354 --> 03:18.822
Dreadwing, what do you ask in return?

03:18.891 --> 03:22.093
Only that you use it wisely.

03:22.161 --> 03:24.462
And? The Omega keys?

03:24.530 --> 03:28.132
In Megatron's possession,
under heaviest guard.

03:28.200 --> 03:32.302
Scream did make a deal with the Cons.

03:32.371 --> 03:33.737
Why?

03:33.806 --> 03:38.008
A shadow of disgrace has been
cast upon the Decepticons.

03:38.077 --> 03:42.113
It is a cause I no
longer wish to be part of.

03:42.181 --> 03:44.749
Then I appeal to you again.

03:44.818 --> 03:48.887
Join us and help end this
conflict once and for all.

03:48.955 --> 03:54.692
Betraying my kind
is not the same as accepting yours.

04:11.776 --> 04:15.511
It's no Star Saber, but I bet
it can shatter Megatron's blade

04:15.580 --> 04:18.012
and put some dents into that
ugly mug of his.

04:18.082 --> 04:19.680
It's not that kind of hammer.

04:19.750 --> 04:23.569
With the Decepticons in possession
of all four Omega keys, a more

04:23.570 --> 04:27.389
appropriate use of the Forge would
be to use it to replicate our own.

04:27.458 --> 04:30.726
Even with such power, their
reconstruction would require

04:30.795 --> 04:32.895
a level of expertise I do not possess.

04:32.963 --> 04:35.898
I guess we better hope
Megatron doesn't destroy the

04:35.967 --> 04:38.468
keys to prevent anyone from ever
going home.

04:38.537 --> 04:40.798
Megatron may be evil,

04:40.926 --> 04:44.742
but I believe he will use the
keys for their intended purpose.

04:44.810 --> 04:49.546
Then I say we let him keep
them and do the work for us.

04:49.615 --> 04:53.594
W... I mean, what difference does
it make who restores Cybertron?

04:53.729 --> 04:59.723
If Megatron revives Cybertron, he will no
doubt use it to his political advantage.

04:59.792 --> 05:01.158
[ stammers ]

05:01.226 --> 05:02.325
Y-you lost me.

05:02.394 --> 05:06.830
In all likelihood, the leader
of the Decepticons will portray

05:06.898 --> 05:12.035
himself as our planet's savior and
brand all Autobots as war criminals.

05:12.103 --> 05:14.637
The grand deception continues.

05:14.706 --> 05:18.474
Megatron's so-called
"achievement" could influence

05:18.543 --> 05:22.611
Cybertron for eons to come,
poisoning the sparks and minds

05:22.680 --> 05:27.649
of its returning citizens ...
hardly the ideal way to begin a new age.

05:27.718 --> 05:31.452
But there is hope.
For while Megatron may have the

05:31.521 --> 05:36.925
keys, he has yet to discover the
existence of the Omega lock itself.

05:36.994 --> 05:40.595
- Omega lock?
- Wait ... now you lost me.

05:40.664 --> 05:43.999
That which the four relics
were designed to activate.

05:44.067 --> 05:48.804
We must locate the device before
Megatron does, and secure it

05:48.873 --> 05:51.040
until we can recover the keys.

05:51.109 --> 05:54.510
There are no more Iacon
entries to decode.

05:54.579 --> 05:57.947
This lock could be anywhere on Earth!

05:58.015 --> 06:01.884
Actually...
it is on Cybertron.

06:01.953 --> 06:02.852
All: What?

06:02.921 --> 06:05.855
- How do you know?
- Alpha Trion revealed its

06:05.924 --> 06:10.093
location to me during the message
conveyed by the Star Saber.

06:10.161 --> 06:13.129
And you didn't think to tell us.

06:13.198 --> 06:17.633
Alpha Trion did not wish it so.

06:20.571 --> 06:22.906
With the Forge of Solus Prime,

06:22.907 --> 06:26.409
we now possess the means
of reaching Cybertron.

06:26.478 --> 06:32.816
I must work quickly, as our tactical
advantage over Megatron will not last long.

06:36.286 --> 06:41.824
<i>Dreadwing.
I have been searching for you.</i>

06:41.892 --> 06:44.659
I am at your service, Lord Megatron.

06:44.728 --> 06:48.830
I recognize that Starscream's
return to our ranks may be...

06:48.898 --> 06:53.701
difficult for you, given the loss
of your twin under his command.

06:53.770 --> 06:56.037
But your cooperation is essential.

06:56.105 --> 06:59.507
We Decepticons will be
best-equipped to rule a restored

06:59.576 --> 07:03.211
Cybertron only if we are united.

07:03.280 --> 07:07.182
Understood.
And if it pleases you, master,

07:07.251 --> 07:11.520
I intend to reach out to
our comrade... personally.

07:12.388 --> 07:15.657
<i>Rise and shine!</i>

07:15.726 --> 07:21.330
Your T-cog transplant was a success.
Yes, I am just that good.

07:21.398 --> 07:22.497
[ sighs ]

07:22.566 --> 07:27.769
Finally. I can't wait to take
flight and soar above the clouds.

07:27.838 --> 07:31.907
<i>Starscream.
I regret to inform you that you</i>

07:31.976 --> 07:36.178
will not live to spread your
wings ever again.

07:43.264 --> 07:45.331
[ yells ]

07:45.400 --> 07:47.800
[ yelps ]

07:47.869 --> 07:49.736
Knockout, help me!

07:49.805 --> 07:52.005
[ scoffs ]

07:55.610 --> 08:00.882
Dreadwing, what has gotten
into you?

08:00.951 --> 08:04.051
[ whimpering ] Wait.
This is about Skyquake, isn't it?

08:04.120 --> 08:06.154
I thought we had put that behind us!

08:06.223 --> 08:08.256
So had I!

08:08.457 --> 08:09.057
Aah!

08:09.126 --> 08:12.294
Casualties are an unfortunate
consequence of war!

08:12.363 --> 08:15.997
But I assure you, your twin met
his end with great honor!

08:16.066 --> 08:20.335
Which you disgraced
by raising him from the dead!

08:20.404 --> 08:23.906
Oh, you know about that.
There must be something I can do,

08:23.974 --> 08:28.177
some form of reparation I can
offer to alleviate your anguish!

08:28.245 --> 08:30.879
Your spark will suffice!

08:31.080 --> 08:34.816
<i>Dreadwing!
Stand down!</i>

08:34.885 --> 08:38.754
This desecrator must pay for
his actions!

08:38.822 --> 08:41.523
You call this loyalty, master?!

08:41.592 --> 08:46.028
I said stand down!
That is an order.

08:46.097 --> 08:49.397
One which I cannot follow.

08:49.466 --> 08:51.333
[ roars ]

08:57.906 --> 08:58.706
[ panting ]

08:58.775 --> 09:00.674
I'm okay? I'm okay!

09:00.743 --> 09:02.409
[ laughs maniacally ]

09:02.478 --> 09:05.780
Lord Megatron, you
have my eternal thanks.

09:05.849 --> 09:10.885
Do not ever make me regret
which one of you I spared.

09:11.720 --> 09:14.556
Is it my imagination, or has
Optimus been acting differently

09:14.625 --> 09:16.858
since that message from Alpha Trion?

09:16.927 --> 09:18.827
[ buzzing ]

09:18.896 --> 09:21.263
Yeah, he has been keeping
things from us.

09:21.332 --> 09:23.232
Even Ratchet's out of the loop.

09:23.300 --> 09:26.535
Well, give me one good reason
Optimus couldn't trust his own

09:26.604 --> 09:29.738
teammates, why he couldn't have
told us about the Omega lock.

09:29.807 --> 09:31.340
Because if he had, Megatron

09:31.408 --> 09:34.009
would've pulled it out of my
head with his patch.

09:34.078 --> 09:38.147
Like it matters. The Cons
are holding all the keys anyway.

09:39.516 --> 09:41.883
Tick tock, Knockout.
Tick tock!

09:41.952 --> 09:45.905
Megatron's expecting results,
and given what we just witnessed,

09:45.906 --> 09:49.858
I would say that we cannot
afford to disappoint our master.

09:49.927 --> 09:54.830
We? Unless nagging counts,
I haven't seen you lift a finger!

09:54.898 --> 09:57.499
I am the one who
brought him the keys.

09:57.568 --> 10:02.304
Do I really need to prove myself further
by deciphering how they operate, too?

10:02.373 --> 10:05.741
Well, perhaps if my research
hadn't been sidelined by

10:05.810 --> 10:09.779
someone's cosmetic surgery,
I might be further along right now!

10:09.848 --> 10:10.680
[ sighs ]

10:10.749 --> 10:14.217
Oh, just give it here!

10:14.286 --> 10:15.685
[ grunting ]

10:15.754 --> 10:18.722
Oh, gee.
Why didn't I think of that?

10:18.790 --> 10:20.857
[ yells ]

10:20.926 --> 10:23.760
[ gasps, growls ]

10:23.829 --> 10:27.164
[ high-pitched whining ]

10:27.232 --> 10:33.838
- Do you think...
- Ready... go!

10:36.074 --> 10:37.641
[ laughs evilly ]

10:37.710 --> 10:41.379
And that is why Dreadwing is
pushing up lug nuts.

10:41.447 --> 10:44.315
And we are not.

10:45.684 --> 10:50.989
Of course! Keys are useless
without something to unlock.

10:51.058 --> 10:54.927
Target the space bridge for Cybertron.

10:54.996 --> 10:58.763
Yet another astonishing
convergence of magic and science,

10:58.832 --> 11:01.532
courtesy of the ancients.

11:01.601 --> 11:05.369
- And our leader.
- It's hard to believe ...

11:05.438 --> 11:08.305
a few swings of that hammer, and bam!

11:09.374 --> 11:13.978
Our ground bridge
is now a space bridge.

11:14.046 --> 11:16.881
Our sensors are detecting a
massive Energon burst occurring

11:16.950 --> 11:18.182
outside Earth's atmosphere.

11:18.251 --> 11:20.785
A surge of that kind could
only mean one thing ...

11:20.786 --> 11:23.320
activation of another space bridge.

11:23.389 --> 11:27.424
Megatron has discovered that
the Omega lock is on Cybertron.

11:27.493 --> 11:30.261
It appears we have
lost our advantage.

11:30.329 --> 11:34.265
But with Megatron unaware
that we now possess the means of

11:34.334 --> 11:40.939
interstellar travel, the element
of surprise remains in our favor.

11:41.208 --> 11:47.379
<i>We must embark on this mission
with every resource at our disposal.</i>

12:18.144 --> 12:23.282
Starscream.
Assume command in my absence.

12:23.351 --> 12:24.350
[ gasps ]

12:24.418 --> 12:27.286
I would be honored, master.

12:38.396 --> 12:40.931
[ metallic pounding ]

12:42.533 --> 12:45.936
What's he forging now?

12:46.005 --> 12:47.371
[ metal clangs ]

13:00.453 --> 13:05.757
Megatron must be stopped,
no matter the cost.

13:40.279 --> 13:43.982
According to the landmarks
displayed by the keys,

13:44.051 --> 13:49.387
the object we seek is located
deep the within the sea of rust.

13:54.594 --> 13:56.795
[ beeping ]

13:56.864 --> 13:58.397
Ah! Optimus?

13:58.466 --> 13:59.899
<i>Uh, n-no, Ratchet.
It's Jack.</i>

13:59.967 --> 14:02.168
Is something wrong?
'Cause school's been out for

14:02.236 --> 14:04.570
almost an hour, and no one's
showed to pick us up.

14:04.639 --> 14:07.079
That is because the
entire team is rather...

14:07.080 --> 14:08.707
indisposed at the moment.

14:08.776 --> 14:12.143
<i>I suggest you obtain an
alternate method of transport.</i>

14:12.212 --> 14:14.712
- What's he saying?
- The bots are busy.

14:14.781 --> 14:16.982
Then tell Ratchet to come get us!

14:17.050 --> 14:20.119
<i>It's not like he has
anything else to do!</i>

14:20.187 --> 14:23.656
Just go home!
I will be in touch later!

14:23.725 --> 14:26.526
He... hello?
He hung up.

14:26.594 --> 14:28.828
What crawled up
his tailpipe and died?

14:28.897 --> 14:31.097
Did Ratchet tell you what's going on?

14:31.166 --> 14:35.302
No. They seem to be keeping
us in the dark a lot lately.

14:38.306 --> 14:40.507
[ device beeping ]

14:51.619 --> 14:54.487
Wha... what just happened?

14:59.961 --> 15:03.230
Smokescreen?
But that's impossible.

15:03.298 --> 15:05.365
The Autobots do not
possess the means to ...

15:05.434 --> 15:07.801
[ deep buzzing ]

15:17.445 --> 15:19.312
Crush them!

15:55.415 --> 15:57.783
Defend the keys!

16:27.117 --> 16:28.984
[ growls ]

16:40.731 --> 16:43.199
[ roars ]

16:43.268 --> 16:48.705
I bested your little blade once,
and I shall do it again!

16:54.579 --> 16:56.447
[ roars ]

17:50.169 --> 17:55.474
I will have those keys,
or I will have your sparks!

17:56.909 --> 18:00.312
I can help with the last part.

18:00.381 --> 18:03.248
The spark extractor!

18:07.052 --> 18:08.919
[ zapping ]

18:19.830 --> 18:21.698
[ roars ]

18:25.902 --> 18:29.405
[ zapping fades ]

18:29.474 --> 18:31.340
[ whoosh, slam ]

18:36.280 --> 18:39.882
Starscream! The Autobots
have seized the Omega keys.

18:39.951 --> 18:43.320
Send reinforcements immediately!

18:43.588 --> 18:46.857
Actually, lord Megatron,
Soundwave has been briefing me

18:46.926 --> 18:52.497
on recent developments, and we
may have a more effective solution.

19:02.074 --> 19:03.842
Our head start won't last long.

19:03.910 --> 19:06.544
This is where Alpha Trion
said we'd find it, right?

19:06.613 --> 19:09.220
These are the coordinates.

19:13.752 --> 19:16.220
Doesn't look like much.

19:19.958 --> 19:24.528
<i>Ratchet, we have
located the Omega lock.</i>

19:24.597 --> 19:25.696
[ sighs ]

19:25.765 --> 19:27.231
At last.

19:27.299 --> 19:29.667
According to Alpha Trion,

19:29.736 --> 19:34.773
the Omega lock is a conduit
to the very Allspark itself.

19:34.842 --> 19:39.178
Optimus, an honor like this
shouldn't belong to me.

19:39.246 --> 19:42.447
[ high-pitched whining ]

19:46.586 --> 19:49.455
[ deep humming ]

20:38.100 --> 20:42.571
<i>Autobots, I would suggest
that you put a halt to your task</i>

20:42.640 --> 20:47.376
- ...and hand over those keys.
- And why would we do that?

20:57.654 --> 21:01.856
So that I may hand over the humans.

21:09.165 --> 21:11.113
And if we refuse?

21:11.614 --> 21:15.813
Then I will have no choice
but to open the pods,

21:15.814 --> 21:20.942
exposing your pets to
Cybertron's toxic atmosphere.

21:21.011 --> 21:27.882
And then we can all watch them
instantly perish, together.

